<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">
  <PropertyGroup>
    <TargetFrameworks>net8.0;net10.0</TargetFrameworks>
    <ImplicitUsings>enable</ImplicitUsings>
    <Nullable>enable</Nullable>
    <PackageId>FluxFlow.Components.Storage</PackageId>
    <AssemblyName>FluxFlow.Components.Storage</AssemblyName>
    <RootNamespace>FluxFlow.Components.Storage</RootNamespace>
    <Version>2.0.0</Version>
    <Authors>FluxFlow contributors</Authors>
    <Description>Standalone storage nodes for FluxFlow: blockified put/get/query/delete over an injected IStorageStore, with broadcast result/error/event ports. No engine required.</Description>
    <PackageTags>workflow;dataflow;components;storage;records</PackageTags>
    <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>
    <PackageReleaseNotes>Rebuilt as standalone storage.put/get/query/delete nodes over an injected IStorageStore: request in, result broadcast out, failures on the error port, diagnostics on the event port. Every message travels as a FlowMessage&lt;T&gt; envelope so the correlation id flows request -&gt; result (and onto the Found/NotFound and Records branches). The storage.store resource node and its connect/disconnect lifecycle are removed — the host owns the IStorageStore lifetime and injects the opened store into each node, exactly like the HTTP node over an HttpClient. The engine factory/module/registration/designer-metadata glue is removed; the nodes depend only on FluxFlow.Nodes and run without the engine. The IStorageStore contract, all request/result/record DTOs, options, error codes, and the store factory/lease/context types are unchanged, so the FileSystem and SqlFile adapters keep working.</PackageReleaseNotes>
    <RepositoryType>git</RepositoryType>
    <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>
    <IncludeSymbols>true</IncludeSymbols>
    <SymbolPackageFormat>snupkg</SymbolPackageFormat>
  </PropertyGroup>
  <ItemGroup>
    <ProjectReference Include="..\FluxFlow.Nodes\FluxFlow.Nodes.csproj" />
  </ItemGroup>
  <ItemGroup>
    <PackageReference Include="System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow" Version="9.0.4" NoWarn="NU1510" />
  </ItemGroup>
  <ItemGroup>
    <None Include="README.md" Pack="true" PackagePath="\" />
  </ItemGroup>
</Project>
